    <items>
        <item id="i63439186488101964aab5105bee6b9cfe">
            <label key="6d89c448b520c254a039bf6caad6e21f">
                <text>Which of these are reasons scientists classify organisms?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="89b1c1de80f35eb0f385836481797561">
                <text>Select all correct answers.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fa10a764d551873052fceb963c5ac18f">
                <text>to allow clear communication between scientists </text>
            </label>
            <label key="bd0b29c7e69a1df6aa5b1a3ea822fdca">
                <text>to ensure that related organisms have the same species names</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e549b8823f8bf25bcdc46eca3035752e">
                <text>to make decisions about which organisms are useful to humans</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c9c39e45eca5a078a714b6922ec8b899">
                <text>to better understand evolutionary relationships between organisms</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i6343921e68bad130379f7745b82e4f78c1">
            <label key="70b6d7d13e38fac9e7678da46b6501db">
                <text>Scientists can use the graph to predict the overall extinction risk for each group.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="78a52656c509a700f4ba345152f928c6">
                <text><br/>Which group can scientists be most certain of its overall extinction risk?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="75c73f175a85cee384f32a5608eb67d1">
                <text>birds</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c4a317a734a700eb6f767bdc511c1588">
                <text>amphibians</text>
            </label>
            <label key="09674ef751063afe5935ca6f70ea08f1">
                <text>mammals</text>
            </label>
            <label key="45053265723f59bd84cf4af2b15def8e">
                <text>reptiles</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i634392875f83f11365068caaaa9b1d6240">
            <label key="374f2dbc3ad2e6c628ff67beee5d8281">
                <text>For each animal group, the graph gives the percentage of species that are at extinction risk.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="1cd8541f0b0cf8688619ac180646011d">
                <text>Which one of these four groups has the highest estimated extinction risk?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fb9859640e0203b20ee65768ca097a97">
                <text>Serpentes</text>
            </label>
            <label key="19d189b12e9fce84ad31484c92ece1cb">
                <text>Testudines</text>
            </label>
            <label key="6dafa61a1f227dbf8652947c18aed523">
                <text>Gekkota</text>
            </label>
            <label key="5baa202cf4bc925cb85d80a06a7b4d53">
                <text>Dibamidae</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i6343936baf54d113573a6b428756da7ea2">
            <label key="cb436674a9c2c31a776f259ac32a9dec">
                <text>Of the groups listed in the graph, which one could contain only one species?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e1fa7d1723546c6fc53041d9478e6fe5">
                <text>Write the name of the group in the box.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="85d04479232f85a912677edcffb88f98">
                <text>Explain your reasoning.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63439431eed5e25867f260445b49f58cc">
            <label key="3bfdb8f697fb2aaa39c6caf26ad8f8b1">
                <text>There are only a few species of Monotremata compared to hundreds of species of Caudata.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="2400cbb90cbdff94a4d9d5ffa77f5248">
                <text>Suppose that conservation efforts succeed in changing the status of one species of Monotremata and one species of Caudata from critically endangered/endangered/vulnerable to near threatened/least concern.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8f70f08191520eacd66e4718188bc4e1">
                <text>What impact would this change in status have on the predicted overall extinction risk for these two groups?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="99f10c8e71a432baea3e24b53bf51186">
                <text>increase in Monotremata, negligible change in Caudata</text>
            </label>
            <label key="17f692f6138bafe0b77f7c91117e47b1">
                <text>negligible change in Monotremata, increase in Caudata</text>
            </label>
            <label key="b5c1680480d1d69346e0134afc3bd698">
                <text>decrease in Monotremata, negligible change in Caudata</text>
            </label>
            <label key="08b92806a875e40431f38016be13482e">
                <text>negligible change in Monotremata, decrease in Caudata</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i6343a756c6f6d1136204ccbcf9dd082e64">
            <label key="44a5f59d8304dc70e36195f8dc8b3749">
                <text>Efforts to conserve non-reptile species are often also effective in conserving reptile species.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="414c577c18325305118fb4c5a0f448b0">
                <text>Which one of the following conservation efforts is most likely to benefit reptile species?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="38fbb0dcc5875efa849386779d53fb78">
                <text>genetic studies of rainforest birds</text>
            </label>
            <label key="5fea24bad85ae1872fd74ead74762828">
                <text>conserving habitat of small mammals</text>
            </label>
            <label key="29894712e7758b272d7524d9294d42e3">
                <text>captive breeding programs for frogs that live in snowy mountainous regions</text>
            </label>
            <label key="1ea2daaba9a374b9ba9a9fa38cd3977e">
                <text>conserving breeding habitat of Antarctic penguins</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i6343a7fd48c9d17917f04d5c73a26c4287">
            <label key="0f84471cbb9811a2710801017f3fac84">
                <text>Which one of the following categories of reptiles is least likely to benefit from conservation strategies aimed at other vertebrates?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="02ccfd2ceb68ac203e6aef12f544e56d">
                <text>herbivorous reptiles</text>
            </label>
            <label key="aecf050cf144ff82358a25d23c33ac30">
                <text>reptiles whose habitat area overlaps that of endangered birds</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e503a035cfa6ae2581d916966f904469">
                <text>reptiles with the smallest habitat area</text>
            </label>
            <label key="3246676a35312a6c727acf95297b4825">
                <text>reptiles whose habitat has been destroyed by urban development</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i6343a87a1660f11364147c39effff2c952">
            <label key="84377284dbf652b5434249ab41420bb6">
                <text>A news article presents alternative data that suggests that extinction risk for the vertebrates in the graph is much lower than that presented in this graph.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8e0f3275bdf4f8e8368b50d217368568">
                <text>Maria thinks that the article is unreliable, biased, irrelevant, and invalid. Her reasons include the following:</text>
            </label>
            <label key="477ceebb65d0b97951a890b2d35ba513">
                <text>The article was published in a magazine on economics.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="d2ec54ff82f527aef6f96b69709a2106">
                <text>The author did not ask a scientist to review the article.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="48a15a299d76be02ce9d3f8f13f4370f">
                <text>The article referenced data from a study funded by a mining company.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="adbf3ea3ba8e8d8918eff7b0d79637e5">
                <text>The article used data that was collected over 30 years ago.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="d936ed449837b65889d555851e0dd634">
                <text> Which one of the following statements about this article is correct?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="2b86dfb79f742d9c7352a26012126d83">
                <text>Points 2 and 3 make the article irrelevant to the topic of extinction risk.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f1bb440f528147b11b637d92e10e51a2">
                <text>Points 1 and 3 make the data invalid.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c34eb9af5d4f4fbed2ce706d28c7e0ec">
                <text>Points 1, 2 and 4 make the article biased.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fdb0fad7beac866ce2d1254ba15fc8f8">
                <text>Points 2 and 4 make the article less reliable.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
    </items>
